.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='GLOBAL'.Subfile-Templates
:P. The Load-All template serves as an example of a sufficiently complete
application for simple database table maintenance, with the usual functions of
modifying, duplicating, deleting (with query!), viewing, and creating a new
entry.
:P. This text is part of the global help, which is displayed as extended help
text before all other referenced help sections. Hence it's a good place to
provide a brief overview about the application's purpose.
:EHELP.
.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='MAIN/SFLOPTS'.Choices
:XH3.Choices
:P.Valid choices for the :HP1.Opt:EHP1. column are
:PARML.
:PT.2=Change
:PD.Entry is selected for being modified in a separate screen.
:PT.3=Copy
:PD.Entry is selected for being modified in a separate screen. After pressing
Enter, the record isn't changed in the database, but a new record is created.
Restrictions regarding duplicate key values need to be respected.
:PT.4=Delete
:PD.Entry is selected for deletion. Upon pressing Enter, all entries selected
for deletion will be displayed on a secondary subfile screen for further
refining the selection, and possibly cancel all or part of the to-be-deleted
entries.
:PT.5=Display
:PD.Entry is to be selected for being displayed in a separate screen. This also
displays additional fields which aren't shown in the SFL list display.
:EPARML.
:NOTE.A record can only be edited by one workstation at a time. If a record is
already locked by another workstation user, it will be opened for viewing only
on the requesting workstation - yours. Making changes is not possible. For this
reason, the user should avoid opening records for just viewing only with Opt
:HP1.2=Change:EHP1. Using Opt :HP1.5=Display:EHP1. is more friendly to
concurrent users, as it allows other operators to change the record, because the
user (you) has then not unnecessarily locked the record for editing.:ENOTE.
:EHELP.
.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='SFLHDR/OPT'.Opt Column
:XH3.Opt Column
:P.A selection number is entered in this column to both select the record and
specify what the system should do with this record.
:EHELP.
.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='SFLHDR/KEYVAL'.Value Column
:XH3.Value Column
:P.A numeric value is shown here.
:EHELP.
.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='SFLHDR/VALFLD'.Text Column
:XH3.Text Column
:P.A short text string is shown here.
:EHELP.
.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='MAIN/SFLDTA'.Data Display Area
:XH3.Data Display Area
:P. Here, some records from the entire set of existing records are displayed.
Changes cannot be made directly. The previously mentioned selections in the Opt
column are there for this purpose. Changes to the records can't be done
directly. These can be employed by specifying the proper :HP1.Opt:EHP1. value.
:P.An indicator is shown at the bottom right corner of the tabular display area:
:PARML.
:PT.More ...
:PD.More records are available which can be shown by pressing the PgDown key.
:PT.End
:PD.The end of the list is reached. No more records are available.
:PARML.
:NOTE.Opt-Selections are lost while paging through the list.:ENOTE.
:EHELP.
.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='MAIN/SFLBTM'.Function Keys
:XH3.Function Keys
:PARML.
:PT.F1=Help
:PD.Provides additional information about using the display or a specific field
on the display.
:PT.F3=Exit
:PD.Ends the current task and returns to the display from which the task was
started.
:PT.F5=Refresh
:PD.Reloads the SFL with records from the database file.
:PT.F6=Add entry
:PD.Calls up the display for entering a new entry (record) into the database
file.
:PT.F12=Cancel
:PD.Returns to the previous menu or display.
:EPARML.
:EHELP.
.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='MAIN/SFLND'.No records to display
:XH3.No records to display
:P.This pseudo-record appears when no records could be found for the list
display.
:P.Possible causes include an empty database file.
:EHELP.
.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='DETAIL/MODE'.Mode
:XH3.Mode
:P.In this area, the current display mode is shown.
:PARML.
:PT.Add New Entry
:PD.If :HP1.F6=Neu:EHP1. was issued, all data bearing fields are emptied. If Opt
:HP1.3=Duplizieren:EHP1. was issued, all data bearing fields contain the data
from the selected base record. Pressing enter creates a new record in the
database file.
:PT.Change Entry
:PD.The current values of the selected record are shown in editable fields for
correction.
:PT.Display Entry
:PD.The current values of the selected record are shown in read only fields for
viewing purposes.
:EPARML.
:EHELP.
.* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP NAME='DETAIL/OPTIONS'.Operations
:XH3.Operations
:P.In this area, possible operations for the selected record and mode are shown.
:EHELP.
